properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 17 at 3:01AM AKST until February 18 at 6:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...East winds 25 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Deltana and Tanana Flats.

* WHEN...From 6 AM this morning to 6 PM AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong south winds from Isabel Pass could
mix northward to Delta Junction at times, causing gusty, erratic
winds.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM THIS MORNING TO 6 PM AKST TUESDAY
